26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_instmem_nv04.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 07:36:28 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#define nv04_instmem(p) container_of((p), struct nv04_instmem, base)
30#include "priv.h"
31
32#include <core/memory.h>
33#include <core/ramht.h>
34
35#ifdef __NetBSD__
36# define __iomem __nvkm_memory_iomem
37#endif
38
39struct nv04_instmem {
40 struct nvkm_instmem base;
41 struct nvkm_mm heap;
42};
43
44/******************************************************************************
45 * instmem object implementation
46 *****************************************************************************/
47#define nv04_instobj(p) container_of((p), struct nv04_instobj, memory)
48
49struct nv04_instobj {
50 struct nvkm_memory memory;
51 struct nv04_instmem *imem;
52 struct nvkm_mm_node *node;
53};
54
55static enum nvkm_memory_target
56nv04_instobj_target(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
57{
58 return NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST;
59}
60
61static u64
62nv04_instobj_addr(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
63{
64 return nv04_instobj(memory)->node->offset;
65}
66
67static u64
68nv04_instobj_size(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
69{
70 return nv04_instobj(memory)->node->length;
71}
72
73static void __iomem *
74nv04_instobj_acquire(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
75{
76 struct nv04_instobj *iobj = nv04_instobj(memory);
77 struct nvkm_device *device = iobj->imem->base.subdev.device;
78 return (char __iomem *)bus_space_vaddr(device->mmiot, device->mmioh) +
79 0x700000 + iobj->node->offset;
80}
81
82static void
83nv04_instobj_release(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
84{
85}
86
87static u32
88nv04_instobj_rd32(struct nvkm_memory *memory, u64 offset)
89{
90 struct nv04_instobj *iobj = nv04_instobj(memory);
91 struct nvkm_device *device = iobj->imem->base.subdev.device;
92 return nvkm_rd32(device, 0x700000 + iobj->node->offset + offset);
93}
94
95static void
96nv04_instobj_wr32(struct nvkm_memory *memory, u64 offset, u32 data)
97{
98 struct nv04_instobj *iobj = nv04_instobj(memory);
99 struct nvkm_device *device = iobj->imem->base.subdev.device;
100 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x700000 + iobj->node->offset + offset, data);
101}
102
103static void *
104nv04_instobj_dtor(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
105{
106 struct nv04_instobj *iobj = nv04_instobj(memory);
107 mutex_lock(&iobj->imem->base.subdev.mutex);
108 nvkm_mm_free(&iobj->imem->heap, &iobj->node);
109 mutex_unlock(&iobj->imem->base.subdev.mutex);
110 return iobj;
111}
112
113static const struct nvkm_memory_func
114nv04_instobj_func = {
115 .dtor = nv04_instobj_dtor,
116 .target = nv04_instobj_target,
117 .size = nv04_instobj_size,
118 .addr = nv04_instobj_addr,
119 .acquire = nv04_instobj_acquire,
120 .release = nv04_instobj_release,
121 .rd32 = nv04_instobj_rd32,
122 .wr32 = nv04_instobj_wr32,
123};
124
125static int
126nv04_instobj_new(struct nvkm_instmem *base, u32 size, u32 align, bool zero,
127 struct nvkm_memory **pmemory)
128{
129 struct nv04_instmem *imem = nv04_instmem(base);
130 struct nv04_instobj *iobj;
131 int ret;
132
133 if (!(iobj = kzalloc(sizeof(*iobj), GFP_KERNEL)))
134 return -ENOMEM;
135 *pmemory = &iobj->memory;
136
137 nvkm_memory_ctor(&nv04_instobj_func, &iobj->memory);
138 iobj->imem = imem;
139
140 mutex_lock(&imem->base.subdev.mutex);
141 ret = nvkm_mm_head(&imem->heap, 0, 1, size, size,
142 align ? align : 1, &iobj->node);
143 mutex_unlock(&imem->base.subdev.mutex);
144 return ret;
145}
146
147/******************************************************************************
148 * instmem subdev implementation
149 *****************************************************************************/
150
151static u32
152nv04_instmem_rd32(struct nvkm_instmem *imem, u32 addr)
153{
154 return nvkm_rd32(imem->subdev.device, 0x700000 + addr);
155}
156
157static void
158nv04_instmem_wr32(struct nvkm_instmem *imem, u32 addr, u32 data)
159{
160 nvkm_wr32(imem->subdev.device, 0x700000 + addr, data);
161}
162
163static int
164nv04_instmem_oneinit(struct nvkm_instmem *base)
165{
166 struct nv04_instmem *imem = nv04_instmem(base);
167 struct nvkm_device *device = imem->base.subdev.device;
168 int ret;
169
170 /* PRAMIN aperture maps over the end of VRAM, reserve it */
171 imem->base.reserved = 512 * 1024;
172
173 ret = nvkm_mm_init(&imem->heap, 0, imem->base.reserved, 1);
174 if (ret)
175 return ret;
176
177 /* 0x00000-0x10000: reserve for probable vbios image */
178 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x10000, 0, false,
179 &imem->base.vbios);
180 if (ret)
181 return ret;
182
183 /* 0x10000-0x18000: reserve for RAMHT */
184 ret = nvkm_ramht_new(device, 0x08000, 0, NULL, &imem->base.ramht);
185 if (ret)
186 return ret;
187
188 /* 0x18000-0x18800: reserve for RAMFC (enough for 32 nv30 channels) */
189 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x00800, 0, true,
190 &imem->base.ramfc);
191 if (ret)
192 return ret;
193
194 /* 0x18800-0x18a00: reserve for RAMRO */
195 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x00200, 0, false,
196 &imem->base.ramro);
197 if (ret)
198 return ret;
199
200 return 0;
201}
202
203static void *
204nv04_instmem_dtor(struct nvkm_instmem *base)
205{
206 struct nv04_instmem *imem = nv04_instmem(base);
207 nvkm_memory_del(&imem->base.ramfc);
208 nvkm_memory_del(&imem->base.ramro);
209 nvkm_ramht_del(&imem->base.ramht);
210 nvkm_memory_del(&imem->base.vbios);
211 nvkm_mm_fini(&imem->heap);
212 return imem;
213}
214
215static const struct nvkm_instmem_func
216nv04_instmem = {
217 .dtor = nv04_instmem_dtor,
218 .oneinit = nv04_instmem_oneinit,
219 .rd32 = nv04_instmem_rd32,
220 .wr32 = nv04_instmem_wr32,
221 .memory_new = nv04_instobj_new,
222 .persistent = false,
223 .zero = false,
224};
225
226int
227nv04_instmem_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index,
228 struct nvkm_instmem **pimem)
229{
230 struct nv04_instmem *imem;
231
232 if (!(imem = kzalloc(sizeof(*imem), GFP_KERNEL)))
233 return -ENOMEM;
234 nvkm_instmem_ctor(&nv04_instmem, device, index, &imem->base);
235 *pimem = &imem->base;
236 return 0;
237}
